"        <p>",
"         National Surgical Infection Prevention Project",
"         <sup>",
"          [1]",
"         </sup>",
"        </p>",
"        Guidelines pertaining to specific types of surgery",
"       </td>",
"      </tr>",
"      <tr>",
"       <td>",
"        Cardiac surgery patients with controlled 6 AM postoperative blood glucose",
"       </td>",
"       <td>",
"        Heart surgery patients whose blood sugar (blood glucose) is kept under good control in the days right after surgery",
"       </td>",
"       <td>",
"        <a href=\"file://www.qualitymeasures.ahrq.gov/content.aspx?id=35532\" target=\"_blank\">",
"         file://www.qualitymeasures.ahrq.gov/content.aspx?id=35532",
"        </a>",
"       </td>",
"       <td>",
"        The measure is not based on any clinical guidelines, but two studies have suggested a link between glucose control and lower rates of wound infection in cardiothoracic surgery patients",
"        <sup>",
"         [2,3]",
"        </sup>",
"       </td>",
"      </tr>",
"      <tr>",
"       <td>",
"        Urinary catheter removed on postoperative day 1 (POD 1) or postoperative day 2 (POD 2) with day of surgery being day zero",
"       </td>",
"       <td>",
